        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:03PM AST by NWS San Juan PR</headline>
        <description>At 200 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was reported capable of
producing a waterspout along the coastline from Anasco to Rincon,
moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Waterspouts and wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar and satellite

IMPACT...Waterspouts can easily overturn boats and create locally
hazardous waters. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs
and blow around unsecured objects.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
